CHAPTER XVIII



In Which Discretion Urges Doctor Luke to Lie
Still in a Pool of Water


It was a mean light       this intermittent moonlight:
with the clouds slow and thick, and
the ominous bank of black cloud rising all
the while from the horizon. A man should go
slow in a light like that! But Doctor Luke and
Billy Topsail must make haste. And by and by
