Billy Topsail abstracted his attention. It returned
to the menace.

There it was       the roar of the stream below:
the deep, narrow rush of it, swelling over the
boulders, curling around them, plunging irresistibly
towards the Black Pool ice, and vanishing
into the stifling gloom beneath, in a swift,
black, silent stream, flecked with creamy puffs
of foam. A misstep, a false stone, a lost balance       a
man would then drift fast and helpless,
bruised by the bottom, flung against the boulders
